Increased blood neutrophil extracellular traps (NETs) associated with early life 
stress: translational findings in recent-onset schizophrenia and rodent model.

Corsi-Zuelli F(#)(1)(2), Schneider AH(#)(3)(4), Santos-Silva T(4), Loureiro 
CM(5)(3)(6), Shuhama R(5)(6), Menezes PR(6)(7), Guimarães FS(4), Gomes FV(4), 
Cunha FQ(3)(4), Louzada-Junior P(3)(8), Del-Ben CM(5)(6).

Author information:
(1)Department of Neuroscience and Behaviour, Division of Psychiatry, Ribeirão 
Preto Medical School, University of São Paulo, Ribeirão Preto, São Paulo, 
Brazil. fabiana.zuelli@usp.br.
(2)Center for Research in Inflammatory Diseases - CRID, Ribeirão Preto Medical 
School, University of São Paulo, Ribeirão Preto, São Paulo, Brazil. 
fabiana.zuelli@usp.br.
(3)Center for Research in Inflammatory Diseases - CRID, Ribeirão Preto Medical 
